title: Limbaugh: 'The Media Did Not Make Donald Trump, and They Can't Destroy Him'
text:
Limbaugh: ‘The Media Did Not Make Donald Trump, and They Can’t Destroy Him’ by Josh Feldman | 10:43 am, February 19th, 2017 
Rush Limbaugh weighed in on President Trump ‘s tweet calling the media the “enemy” today, saying, “I think there’s something to it.” 
As they were talking about Barack Obama ‘s first few months compared to President Trump ‘s, Limbaugh said on Fox News Sunday people didn’t want to get in the way of the first black president’s agenda because people didn’t want to be accused of racism. 
He talked to Chris Wallace about the resistance to Trump not just in government but in the press, saying, “The media did not make Donald Trump, and they can’t destroy him.” 
Limbaugh said the liberal press has a “blueprint for destroying Republican political officials they don’t like,” but it won’t work on Trump because he’s not a typical Republican. 
Wallace asked him about the “enemy” tweet, and Limbaugh said Trump’s voters certainly don’t think it went too far. It’s pretty clear to him that many in the press are “enemies of Trump” and they simply don’t understand him and his appeal. 
Watch above, via Fox.
